Marissa Ann Mayer (/ˈmaɪər/; born May 30, 1975) is an American information technology executive, formerly serving as the president and CEO of Yahoo!, a position she had held starting July 2012. In January 2017, it was announced that she will step down from the company's board upon the sale of Yahoo!'s operating business to Verizon Communications.[8] She announced that resignation on June 13, 2017.[9] She is a graduate of Stanford and was a long-time executive, usability leader, and key spokesperson for Google.[10][11][12]



